ckdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2531882\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 17, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104sap1665702769871.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/sap1665702769871.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/sap1665702769871.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"sap1665702769871\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n               \n Migrating from Uniface 10.3 Enterprise Edition\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sap1665702769871__p_d68390e1_d68391e1_d68392e1\">Uniface <span class=\"ph\">10.4</span> adds and enlarges some fields in the Uniface Repository. Consequently, the IDE cannot work with a 10.3 Repository. You must therefore migrate Repository objects from Uniface 10.3 ot Uniface <span class=\"ph\">10.4</span>.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"sap1665702769871__section_bdz_zqy_svb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d780191e61\"> Prepare for Migration </h2>\n<div class=\"p\">\n<ol class=\"ol\" id=\"sap1665702769871__ol_uwf_bry_svb\">\n<li class=\"li\">Review the changes made in Uniface 10. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ntm1665702762212.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ntm1665702762212.html\" title=\"Rocket® Uniface 10.4 features a new licensing management system and Repository changes to enable future Uniface IDE enhancements. In addition there are improvements to enable the Uniface Router Monitor to handle TLS connections, and some significant currency upgrades.\">What's New in Uniface 10.4.01</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lqs1665702762288.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lqs1665702762288.html\">Uniface 10.4.01: Repository Changes</a>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\">Review the <a class=\"xref\" href=\"https://community.rocketsoftware.com/rocket-uniface-forum-home-20/uniface-product-availability-information-18191\" rel=\"external noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Platform Availability Matrix</a> to ensure that your\n            environment supports Uniface 10.</li>\n<li class=\"li\">Ensure that you use a Unicode-enabled database for the Uniface 10 Repository.</li>\n<li class=\"li\">Install Uniface <span class=\"ph\">10.4</span>, if you have not already done\n            so. It automatically creates a default Repository using an SQLite database. For more\n            information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uya1665702742100.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uya1665702742100.html\" title=\"The installation program copies the directories, files, and executables required to run Rocket Uniface, and configures them to run out-of-the box.\">Installing Uniface</a>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\">If you want to use another supported database as your Repository, generate the SQL\n            scripts to create the required Repository tables using the Create Table facility\n              (<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/gensql createtable</span>), then run these scripts in the appropriate\n            DBMS. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gbn1665702541954.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gbn1665702541954.html\" title=\"By default, Uniface uses an SQLite database for its Repository, but you may want to use a different DBMS.\">Generate Scripts for Creating Repository Tables</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cck1665702542032.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cck1665702542032.html\" title=\"The /genSql switch generates DBMS-specific SQL command scripts for preparing an application database or the Uniface Repository, including creating tables and enforcing referential integrity constraints in the database.\">/genSql</a>. </li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"sap1665702769871__section_hgx_1sy_svb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d780191e141\"> Migrate Repository Objects </h2>\n<div class=\"p\">\n<ol class=\"ol\" id=\"sap1665702769871__ol_e3q_dsy_svb\">\n<li class=\"li\">In your Uniface 10.3 installation, export your application definitions to XML files.\n            You can use the Export Repository Objects form (<span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\"> Main Menu ( ≡ ) &gt; Export</span></span>) or the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$ude (\"export\")</span>function in your own export\n            component.</li>\n<li class=\"li\">Import the export file or files into Uniface <span class=\"ph\">10.4</span>.\n            You can:<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"sap1665702769871__ul_l14_hsy_svb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sap1665702769871__li_d31148e1_d31149e1_d31150e1\">In the Uniface IDE, choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Main Menu ( ≡ ) &gt;Import XML</span></span>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sap1665702769871__li_d31151e1_d31152e1_d31153e1\">Run the Uniface IDE\n                  (<span class=\"ph filepath\">ide.exe</span>) with the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/imp</span> command line\n                switch. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xsn1665702696023.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xsn1665702696023.html\" title=\"Import an XML file containing Repository definitions exported from the Uniface Repository.\">/imp</a>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sap1665702769871__li_d31154e1_d31155e1_d31156e1\">Create a component that uses <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$ude\n                  (\"import\")</span> to import the files. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rfn1665702575948.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rfn1665702575948.html\" title=\"Import data into the Repository.\">$ude (\"import\")</a>. </li>\n</ul><p class=\"p\">Uniface will import the data, and then migrate the definitions, and report\n              warnings and errors about potential problems and failures.</p></li>\n<li class=\"li\">Compile the imported objects and test the application. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wyk1665702998988.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wyk1665702998988.html\" title=\"Compile and test the migrated application to identify and correct possible changes in the way the application functions.\">Compile and Test the Migrated Application</a>.</li>\n<li class=\"li\">If you also migrated templates and pallets, you can choose reload the Uniface <span class=\"ph\">10.4</span> templates which were overwritten by the import.\n            Choose <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Main Menu ( ≡ ) &gt; Load Templates</span> and choose\n              <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Load default templates</span>.</li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531882\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531882\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Migrating from Uniface 10.3 Enterprise Edition Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 17, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Migrating from Uniface 10.3 Enterprise Edition Uniface 10.4 adds and enlarges some fields in the Uniface Repository. Consequently, the IDE cannot work with a 10.3 Repository. You must therefore migrate Repository objects from Uniface 10.3 ot Uniface 10.4 . Prepare for Migration Review the changes made in Uniface 10. For more information, see What's New in Uniface 10.4.01 and Uniface 10.4.01: Repository Changes . Review the Platform Availability Matrix to ensure that your environment supports Uniface 10. Ensure that you use a Unicode-enabled database for the Uniface 10 Repository. Install Uniface 10.4 , if you have not already done so. It automatically creates a default Repository using an SQLite database. For more information, see Installing Uniface . If you want to use another supported database as your Repository, generate the SQL scripts to create the required Repository tables using the Create Table facility ( /gensql createtable ), then run these scripts in the appropriate DBMS. For more information, see Generate Scripts for Creating Repository Tables and /genSql . Migrate Repository Objects In your Uniface 10.3 installation, export your application definitions to XML files. You can use the Export Repository Objects form ( Main Menu ( ≡ ) > Export ) or the $ude (\"export\") function in your own export component. Import the export file or files into Uniface 10.4 . You can: In the Uniface IDE, choose Main Menu ( ≡ ) >Import XML . Run the Uniface IDE ( ide.exe ) with the /imp command line switch. For more information, see /imp . Create a component that uses $ude (\"import\") to import the files. For more information, see $ude (\"import\") . Uniface will import the data, and then migrate the definitions, and report warnings and errors about potential problems and failures. Compile the imported objects and test the application. For more information, see Compile and Test the Migrated Application . If you also migrated templates and pallets, you can choose reload the Uniface 10.4 templates which were overwritten by the import. Choose Main Menu ( ≡ ) > Load Templates and choose Load default templates . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}